<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-22T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-22T01:00:00-05:00" n="1426" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1426">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/335.</note>
                            <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-21T23:00:00-07:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 21, 1914, 11 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>General Villa’s decree permitting Spaniards to return to Torreon and
                                Chihuahua will be published in newspapers to-morrow provided for
                                return of all who are conscious of not having taken part in any
                                manner in internal affairs of Mexico. Am forwarding copy of text by
                                mail. This has had good effect and many will return.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">G. C. Carothers</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>